\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 #}{\insrsid13787376  ID_PREFERENCESDIALOG}}}{\insrsid13787376  }{
\cs15\fs18\cf1\up6\insrsid13787376 K{\footnote \pard\plain \s16\ql \li0\ri0\sl-240\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 K}{
\insrsid13787376  Preferences; Dialog Box}}}{\insrsid13787376  }{\b\cf2\insrsid13787376 Preferences Dialog Box}{\insrsid13787376 
\par Select the serial }{\b\insrsid13787376 Port}{\insrsid13787376  (COM 1 through COM 4, or None) that will be used to transfer results of each finished run to another computer. In that computer, run the wpeakc.exe program to receive, display, and save d
ata from the chromatograph. The GC itself displays the results and stores data, but the option of transferring the results to some other computers or other equipments might be very useful, especially in case of necessity to locate the monitoring and/or co
ntrol equipment away from potentially hazardous areas.  
\par In }{\b\insrsid13787376 Load File }{\insrsid13787376 edit box, fill in the desired job file name (xxxxxx.job) to load at startup. Check corresponding check boxes to save the parameters shown on exiting the program. After you finished, open the }{
\uldb\insrsid13787376 Save Options}{\uldb\dbch\af11\insrsid13787376 \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0  Dialog Box}{\v\dbch\af11\insrsid13787376 \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ID_SAVEOPTIONSDIALOG}{\b\insrsid13787376  }{\insrsid13787376 and click }{
\b\insrsid13787376 OK}{\insrsid13787376  to save the parameters.
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb280\sa120\sl-320\slmult0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs24\cf2\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid13787376 \page }{
