\insrsid13787376 , }{\b\insrsid13787376 Sample Time}{\insrsid13787376 , }{\b\insrsid13787376 Inject Time, }{\insrsid13787376 and}{\b\insrsid13787376  Equilibration Time }{\insrsid13787376 Windows in minutes and seconds. 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 b.\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-180\li180\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx270\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls2\adjustright\rin0\lin180\itap0 {\insrsid13787376 
If this GC has two temperature zones, or if the Flame Ionization Detector (}{\b\insrsid13787376 FID}{\insrsid13787376 ) is used, the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Inj/Det. Temp }{\insrsid13787376 
Window is enabled. Fill in the temperature in whole numbers in degrees C. In case of FID, this temperature should be set to >100 C. Otherwise, the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Inj/Det. Temp }{\insrsid13787376 should be set 25-50 C above the }{\b\insrsid13787376 
Oven Temperature}{\insrsid13787376 . This window isn't shown if the GC has only one temperature zone and FID detector is not used.}{\b\insrsid13787376 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 c.\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-180\li180\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx180\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls2\adjustright\rin0\lin180\itap0 {\insrsid13787376 . Select the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Oven Temp }{
\insrsid13787376 Window and fill in the temperature in whole numbers in degrees C. For the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Isothermal Method}{\insrsid13787376  (constant oven temperature), make sure that the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Ramping }{\insrsid13787376 
check box is turned off (no check mark).}{\b\insrsid13787376 
\par }\pard \ql \fi-270\li270\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin270\itap0 {\insrsid13787376 d. In case of }{\b\insrsid13787376 Temperature Programming,}{\insrsid13787376  make sure that the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Ramping }{
\insrsid13787376 check box has a check mark.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\insrsid13787376    1. Set the oven temperature as the initial temperature
\par    2. Fill in the initial }{\b\insrsid13787376 Hold Time 1}{\insrsid13787376 .
\par   3. Fill in the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Ramp 1 }{\insrsid13787376 and }{\b\insrsid13787376 Ramp 2 }{\insrsid13787376 rates (1- 5 degree/min. or any ramp rate that desired and acceptable).
\par    4. Fill in the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Hold Temp 2 }{\insrsid13787376 and }{\b\insrsid13787376 Hold Temp 3 }{\insrsid13787376 temperatures, in degrees C.
\par    5. Fill in the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Hold Time 2 }{\insrsid13787376 and }{\b\insrsid13787376 Hold Time 3 }{\insrsid13787376 in minutes.
\par e. In }{\b\insrsid13787376 Misc. Table}{\insrsid13787376 : 
\par         Check desired check boxes to enable corresponding actions and processes:
\par \tab }{\b\insrsid13787376 Alarm}{\insrsid13787376  - enable/disable all alarms;
\par }\pard \ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\insrsid13787376 \tab }{\b\insrsid13787376 Avg}{\insrsid13787376  (averages) - enables calcula
tions and output of Avg, Min, and Max concentrations of each component in each point during the Avg cycle (shift time);
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\insrsid13787376         Fill in (in whole hours), or leave the default values for the time intervals of
\par }\pard \ql \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\insrsid13787376 \tab }{\b\insrsid13787376 Avg cycle }{\insrsid13787376 - the duration of the Avg cycle in a 
Continuous Run Mode, 1 to 8 hours.  Avg, Min, and Max results are zeroed at the beginning of the new cycle; 
\par \tab }{\b\insrsid13787376 Calibration Cycle }{\insrsid13787376 - time interval between automatic calibrations In a Continuous or Repeat Run Modes, 0 to 24 hours. If it is set to 0, no calibration run will be forced.
\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\b\insrsid13787376 Repeat Cycle  }{\insrsid13787376 - the period for the system to fulfill a single scan through all the active points.
\par }{\b\insrsid13787376 2}{\b\super\insrsid13787376 nd}{\b\insrsid13787376  Pump }{\insrsid13787376 -  turns the 2}{\super\insrsid13787376 nd}{\insrsid13787376  pump ON/OFF. 
