\insrsid13787376  Detector Dialog Box}}}{\insrsid13787376  }{\cs15\fs18\cf1\up6\insrsid13787376 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s16\ql \li0\ri0\sl-240\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 #}{\insrsid13787376  ID_DETECTORDIALOG}}}{\insrsid13787376  }{\cs15\fs18\cf1\up6\insrsid13787376 K{\footnote \pard\plain \s16\ql \li0\ri0\sl-240\slmult1
\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 K}{\insrsid13787376  Detector; Dialog Box}}}{\insrsid13787376  Detector Dialog Box
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid13787376 
In this dialog box, you can set the parameters of processing the detector signals and sending the analysis results to analog outputs:  }{\uldb\insrsid13787376 
\par }{\insrsid13787376 a. }{\b\insrsid13787376 On/Off }{\insrsid13787376 check box to enable/disable the detector.
\par b. If the detector is of }{\b\insrsid13787376 FUV-type }{\insrsid13787376 and the check box is checked, the operation sequence and the signal processing is changed to measure and display an optical absorbance of the sample.
\par c. }{\b\insrsid13787376 Noise and Baseline }{\insrsid13787376 measurements are set with the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Time}{\insrsid13787376  and }{\b\insrsid13787376 Length}{\insrsid13787376  edit boxes.
\par d. }{\b\insrsid13787376 Segment Width }{\insrsid13787376 (whole numbers, 1 to 30) allows a signal averaging over the number of data points.
\par e. The }{\b\insrsid13787376 Peak Detection }{\insrsid13787376 algorithm can be set to }{\b\insrsid13787376 Baseline Projection, Tangent Skimming, }{\insrsid13787376 or }{\b\insrsid13787376 Peaks Deconvolute}{\insrsid13787376 .
\par f. The concentration can be calculated on }{\b\insrsid13787376 Peak Height }{\insrsid13787376 or }{\b\insrsid13787376 Peak Area }{\insrsid13787376 data.
\par g. The }{\b\insrsid13787376 Range}{\insrsid13787376  field can be set to 1, 10, or 100, with the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Range=1}{\insrsid13787376  being of the highest gain.
\par i. }{\b\insrsid13787376 4-20 mA Range }{\insrsid13787376 edit boxes allow setting individually for each
 component or point the concentration values that would result in the maximum value of the analog output (20 mA), with 4 mA output to be at zero concentration.
\par j. }{\b\insrsid13787376 Lamp Save }{\insrsid13787376 check box allows increasing the PID lamp life time by turning the lamp ON only in the time intervals around the peak retention times of the active components in the sample, and OFF between the peaks. 

\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sl-240\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\insrsid13787376 k. If the }{\b\insrsid13787376 External}{\insrsid13787376 
 check box is checked, a signal from an external detector is averaged over the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Peak RT}{\insrsid13787376  +- }{\b\insrsid13787376 Window}{\insrsid13787376  time interval (set in the }{\b\uldb\insrsid13787376 Components}{
\v\insrsid13787376 ID_COMPONENTSDIALOG}{\insrsid13787376  dialog box).
\par }\pard\plain \s16\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid13787376 
