Component Names }{\insrsid13787376 and the process parameters related to a specific component, such as }{\b\insrsid13787376 Retention Time}{\insrsid13787376 , }{\b\insrsid13787376 Window}{\insrsid13787376 , }{\b\insrsid13787376 Response Factor}{
\insrsid13787376 , and a }{\b\insrsid13787376 Low }{\insrsid13787376 and }{\b\insrsid13787376 High Alarm }{\insrsid13787376 levels. To set parameters for any component; click on the corresponding line (click the first blank line if you are fillin
g in a new component) and then click on the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Edit}{\insrsid13787376  button. An }{\uldb\insrsid13787376 Edit Component Dialog Box}{\v\dbch\af11\insrsid13787376 \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ID_EDITCOMPONENTDIALOG}{\insrsid13787376 
 will pop up which allows to edit the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Component\rquote s Name, Retention Time}{\insrsid13787376 , }{\b\insrsid13787376 Window}{\insrsid13787376 , }{\b\insrsid13787376 Response Factor}{\insrsid13787376 , }{\b\insrsid13787376 Low Alarm 
}{\insrsid13787376 and }{\b\insrsid13787376 High Alarm}{\insrsid13787376 , and also to turn the component }{\b\insrsid13787376 on/off}{\insrsid13787376 . When finished, click }{\b\insrsid13787376 OK}{\insrsid13787376 
 and continue with the next component if needed. Then click }{\b\insrsid13787376 OK}{\insrsid13787376 .
