\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 #}{\insrsid13787376  }{\dbch\af11\insrsid13787376 \hich\af0\dbch\af11\loch\f0 ID_CALIBRATIONDIALOG}}}{\cf1\insrsid13787376  }{\cs15\fs18\cf1\up6\insrsid13787376 K
{\footnote \pard\plain \s16\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 K}{\insrsid13787376  Calibration Graph; Calibration}}}
{\insrsid13787376  Calibration Graph Window
\par }{\b0\cf1\insrsid13787376 The graph displays the concentration of the selected component as a function of the component's peak height. In case of a multiple stan
dard calibration, the graph is drawn as straight lines between the successive calibration points from the calibration runs made with available standards (the origin is included as the case of zero concentration), and reflects the linear approximation appr
oach between the calibration points nearest to the measured one (the calibration points just above and below the particular peak height) used in calculations of the concentrations of the components f
rom the analysis data. If case the calibration was done with the only standard, the linear approximation is used (a straight line through the calibration point and the origin).
\par }{\insrsid13787376 \page }{\cs15\fs18\cf1\up6\insrsid13787376 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s16\ql \li0\ri0\sl-240\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
