\fs20\insrsid13787376  }{\b\cf2\insrsid13787376 Troubleshooting}{\insrsid13787376 
\par }\pard\plain \s16\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid13787376 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid13787376 
Info messages at the bottom of the main window show the current operation being executed by the GC. However, if some important parameters/conditions are beyond the normal limits, the diagnostics alarm signal is sent out, and the following messages infor
m you on the errors:
\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\b\cf6\insrsid13787376 Lamp error}{\insrsid13787376  \endash  the FID or PID lamp or/and the High Voltage Board are not working properly. 
\par }{\b\cf6\insrsid13787376 Oven temperature low}{\insrsid13787376  - the oven temperature was 10 or more degrees below the value set as the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Oven Temperature}{\insrsid13787376  in the }{\uldb\insrsid13787376 Method Dialog Box}{
\v\insrsid13787376 ID_METHODDIALOG}{\insrsid13787376 . The message disappears, and the diagnostics alarm goes OFF, if the temperature is back to no more than 2 degrees below the }{\b\insrsid13787376 Oven Temperature}{\insrsid13787376  value.
\par }{\b\cf6\insrsid13787376 A/D board error}{\b\insrsid13787376  }{\insrsid13787376 \endash  the A/D board is not functioning properly. This results in incorrect reading the tem
peratures and the detector signals. The message disappears, and the diagnostics alarm goes OFF, if the board functioning is restored. Otherwise, the GC should be turned off, and the board should be replaced. 
\par }{\b\cf6\insrsid13787376 Calibration failed in continuous mode}{\b\insrsid13787376  }{\insrsid13787376 \endash  the cal
ibration failed three times in a row, and the GC operation has been stopped. Check if the retention time of the calibration gas peak on the chromatogram corresponds to the value set in the }{\uldb\insrsid13787376 Standard Dialog Box}{\v\insrsid13787376 
ID_STANDARDSDIALOG}{\insrsid13787376 . Check if the calibration gas cylinder is not empty.
\par \page }{\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s16\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 $}{
\insrsid13787376  Standard List Dialog Box}}}{\insrsid13787376  }{\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s16\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 #}{\insrsid13787376  ID_STANDARDLIST}}}{\insrsid13787376  }{\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 K{\footnote \pard\plain 
\s16\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs15\fs18\up6\insrsid13787376 K}{\insrsid13787376  Standards; Standards, list}}}{\insrsid13787376  }{
\b\cf2\insrsid13787376 Standard List Dialog Box
\par }{\insrsid13787376 This dialog box prompts you to select the Standard # (one of four available) to which the calibration results will be assigned to. The known concentration of this standard sample should be shown in the Calibration }{
\uldb\insrsid13787376 Standards Dialog Box}{\v\insrsid13787376 ID_STANDARDSDIALOG}{\insrsid13787376 . With multi-standard calibration, the concentration of the analyte will be calculat
ed from the closest two standards. In case of only one calibration standard used, the analyte concentration is calculated from the linear approximation between the origin and the calibration standard point. 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb280\sa120\sl-320\slmult0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs24\cf2\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b0\insrsid13787376 \page }{
